                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>On the south wall of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the central shrine in the Śivāṅkureśvara temple.</p>						
                            
                            <p>This incomplete record engraved in Grantha characters gives a number of birudas including <hi rend="italic">Ayyaṅgamalaparāyara Gaṇḍagaṇḍagopāla-śirah-kantu[for ndu]ka-krīḍāvinoda Pāṇḍya-sthāpanāchārya</hi>, apparently of a Hoysala king. Palaographically it may be assigned to the 13-14th century A.D.</p>						
                            
                        </summary>
                    </msContents>
